{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848410291,"sessionID":"ses_287320da7ffeIRXDHK3AUejGkQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78d04c8a001M0Kap6r9AEyHqU","messageID":"msg_d78ceedfc001pShRcPiWe4GewX","sessionID":"ses_287320da7ffeIRXDHK3AUejGkQ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-2169f1abd4524d04afdf6e34e3492e58","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md","content":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Types & Constants (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Define `GarbageCollectorStats` struct for stats retrieval\n  - Fields: `Interval`, `OnceTimeout`, `IdleTimeout`\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:129-133`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n\n- [x] **T1.2**: Define GC constants in `defaults.go`\n  - `GarbageCollectorInterval = 2 * time.Minute`\n  - `GCBatchSize = 16`\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:9` and `defaults.go:17`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval -v`\n\n### Phase 2: GarbageCollector Struct & Constructor (ST-2)\n\n- [x] **T2.1**: Define `GarbageCollector` struct with all required fields\n  - Fields: `manager`, `interval`, `onceTimeout`, `stopCh`, `wg`, `logger`, `idleTimeout`, `idleMu`\n  - Thread-safe: `idleMu sync.RWMutex` protects `idleTimeout`\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:11-20`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.2**: Implement `NewGarbageCollector` constructor\n  - Apply defaults if `interval == 0`: use `GarbageCollectorInterval`\n  - Apply defaults if `onceTimeout == 0`: use `2 * time.Minute`\n  - Initialize `idleTimeout` from `manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout`\n  - Create `stopCh := make(chan struct{})`\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:22-38`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector -v && go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval -v`\n\n### Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods (ST-3)\n\n- [x] **T3.1**: Implement `Start()` method\n  - Call `gc.wg.Add(1)`\n  - Launch `go gc.runLoop()`\n  - Non-blocking, returns immediately\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:46-49`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v`\n\n- [x] **T3.2**: Implement `Stop()` method\n  - Call `close(gc.stopCh)` to signal shutdown\n  - Call `gc.wg.Wait()` to block until goroutine completes\n  - Returns only after goroutine exits\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:51-54`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v`\n\n- [x] **T3.3**: Implement `runLoop()` background ticker loop\n  - Run in separate goroutine\n  - Execute `runOnce(ctx)` immediately on start\n  - Create `ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)`\n  - Loop on `select { <-stopCh, <-ticker.C }`\n  - On `stopCh`: log `\"garbage collector stopped\"` and return\n  - On `ticker.C`: call `runOnce(context.Background())`\n  - Defer `gc.wg.Done()` and `ticker.Stop()`\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:56-73`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v`\n\n### Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic (ST-4)\n\n- [x] **T4.1**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` with context timeout protection\n  - Create `ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)`\n  - Capture current time: `now := time.Now()`\n  - Get current `idleTimeout` via `gc.getIdleTimeout()`\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:75-80`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired -v`\n\n- [x] **T4.2**: Implement expired sandbox query logic\n  - Call `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)`\n  - Log error if query fails: `\"failed to list expired sandboxes\"`\n  - Return error if query fails\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:82-86`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired -v`\n\n- [x] **T4.3**: Implement inactive sandbox query logic\n  - Calculate `inactiveBefore := now.Add(-idleTimeout)`\n  - Call `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)`\n  - Log error if query fails: `\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\"`\n  - Return error if query fails\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:88-93`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive -v`\n\n- [x] **T4.4**: Implement batch deletion loop\n  - Merge expired and inactive lists: `allSandboxes := append(expired, inactive...)`\n  - For each sandbox, call `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)`\n  - Handle `NotFoundError`: silently ignore (continue)\n  - Handle other errors: log `\"gc delete failed\"` and continue\n  - Log successful deletion: `\"gc deleted sandbox\"` with reason\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:95-108`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError -v`\n\n- [x] **T4.5**: Implement batch size limit enforcement\n  - Verify at most `GCBatchSize` (16) items per category processed\n  - Ensure store size decreases appropriately after cleanup\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:82-93` (limit param)\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit -v`\n\n### Phase 5: Runtime Configuration Methods (ST-5)\n\n- [x] **T5.1**: Implement `SetIdleTimeout(timeout)` method\n  - Acquire `gc.idleMu.Lock()`\n  - Update `gc.idleTimeout`\n  - Release mutex\n  - Thread-safe for concurrent access\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:113-117`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n\n- [x] **T5.2**: Implement `getIdleTimeout()` internal method\n  - Acquire `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n  - Return current `gc.idleTimeout`\n  - Release mutex\n  - Thread-safe for concurrent reads\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:40-44`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n\n- [x] **T5.3**: Implement `GetStats()` stats retrieval method\n  - Acquire `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n  - Return `GarbageCollectorStats{Interval, OnceTimeout, IdleTimeout}`\n  - Release mutex\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:119-127`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n\n### Phase 6: Concurrent Safety (ST-6)\n\n- [x] **T6.1**: Implement thread-safe idleTimeout access\n  - Add `idleMu sync.RWMutex` to `GarbageCollector` struct\n  - Protect all reads/writes to `idleTimeout`\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:18-20`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce -v`\n\n- [x] **T6.2**: Implement concurrent cleanup safety\n  - Multiple `runOnce()` calls can execute concurrently\n  - No race conditions on store operations\n  - No race conditions on idleTimeout reads\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:75-111`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -race -run TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce -v`\n\n### Phase 7: Store Integration (ST-7)\n\n- [x] **T7.1**: Add `ListExpiredSandboxes` to Store interface\n  - Method signature: `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Query sandboxes where `ExpiresAt < before`\n  - Sort by `ExpiresAt` ascending (oldest first)\n  - Limit to `limit` items\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go:29` and `store.go:90-110`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestListExpired -v`\n\n- [x] **T7.2**: Add `ListInactiveSandboxes` to Store interface\n  - Method signature: `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Query sandboxes where `LastActivity < before` (skip zero `LastActivity`)\n  - Sort by `LastActivity` ascending (most inactive first)\n  - Limit to `limit` items\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go:30` and `store.go:112-132`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestListInactive -v`\n\n- [x] **T7.3**: Implement MemoryStore GC query methods\n  - Use `sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe reads\n  - Implement sorting for deterministic cleanup order\n  - Implement limit truncation for batch size enforcement\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go:90-132`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go -v`\n\n### Phase 8: Deletion Reason Classification (ST-8)\n\n- [x] **T8.1**: Implement `determineDeletionReason` helper function\n  - If `now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`: return `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n  - If `!sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero()` AND `now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`: return `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n  - Otherwise: return `DeletionReasonUserRequest`\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go:167-175`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestDetermineDeletionReason -v`\n\n### Phase 9: Integration & Validation (ST-9)\n\n- [x] **T9.1**: Integrate GC with SandboxLifecycleManager\n  - GC delegates deletion to `manager.DeleteSandbox`\n  - Manager handles K8s resource deletion + store cleanup\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:98`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired -v`\n\n- [x] **T9.2**: Verify error handling flow\n  - NotFound errors silently ignored\n  - List errors abort cycle but don't crash GC\n  - Delete errors logged but continue processing\n  - GC restarts on next ticker cycle after errors\n  - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:82-108`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError -v`\n\n- [x] **T9.3**: All unit tests pass\n  - `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run GarbageCollector -v`\n  - Coverage: >80% for garbage_collector.go\n  - No race conditions\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run GarbageCollector -v`\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nT1.1 → T1.2\n  ↓\nT2.1 → T2.2\n  ↓\nT3.1 → T3.2 → T3.3\n  ↓\nT4.1 → T4.2 → T4.3 → T4.4 → T4.5\n  ↓\nT5.1 → T5.2 → T5.3\n  ↓\nT6.1 → T6.2\n  ↓\nT7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3\n  ↓\nT8.1\n  ↓\nT9.1 → T9.2 → T9.3\n```\n\n---\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n| Task | Verification Command |\n|------|----------------------|\n| All GC tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run GarbageCollector -v` |\n| Constructor tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector -v` |\n| Lifecycle tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v` |\n| Cleanup tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce -v` |\n| Concurrent safety | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -race -run TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce -v` |\n| Test coverage | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep garbage_collector` |\n| Build verification | `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n| Lint check | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [x] GarbageCollector runs as background goroutine with ticker loop\n- [x] Immediate cleanup on start, then periodic cleanup every `interval`\n- [x] Graceful shutdown via `Stop()` with `WaitGroup` synchronization\n- [x] Expired sandbox cleanup based on `ExpiresAt` timestamp\n- [x] Inactive sandbox cleanup based on `LastActivity` + `idleTimeout`\n- [x] Batch size limit: max 16 items per category per cycle\n- [x] NotFound errors silently ignored (already deleted)\n- [x] Other errors logged but don't stop cleanup cycle\n- [x] Thread-safe `idleTimeout` runtime configuration via `SetIdleTimeout`\n- [x] Stats retrieval via `GetStats()` for monitoring\n- [x] Store methods: `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n- [x] Deletion reason classification: `MaxDurationReached`, `IdleTimeout`, `UserRequest`\n- [x] All unit tests pass (9 tests)\n- [x] No race conditions detected\n\n---\n\n## Files Modified/Created\n\n| File | Status | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | ✓ Complete | GarbageCollector implementation (133 lines) |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | ✓ Complete | Comprehensive test suite (9 tests, 379 lines) |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | ✓ Complete | Added ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | ✓ Complete | Added GC methods to Store interface |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | ✓ Complete | Added determineDeletionReason helper |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | ✓ Complete | Added GarbageCollectorInterval constant |\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n- **Implementation 100% complete**\n- **All 9 tests pass with full coverage**\n- **Thread-safe implementation**: `idleMu sync.RWMutex` protects `idleTimeout` for concurrent access\n- **Graceful degradation**: GC continues processing even if individual deletions fail\n- **Batch processing**: Limit of 16 items per category prevents resource exhaustion\n- **Context timeout protection**: Single GC cycle limited to `onceTimeout` (default 2 minutes)\n- **Integration**: GC delegates deletion to `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox`\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Timeline\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n|-------|-------|--------|------------|\n| Phase 1: Core Types & Constants | T1.1, T1.2 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n| Phase 2: Struct & Construct